<dl id="n08158j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08158j">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08158j"> 158(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 1 Scotch pound / = 1.80 </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Through gradual debasement of the coinage, the &lsquo;pound Scots&rsquo;, originally the same as the English, was at the Union of the Crowns equal to one twelfth of a pound sterling, being divided into 20 shillings each of the value of an English penny.</mm> </dd></dl>
